##Soaked for six hours in their protective suits, they spent New Year's Eve looking for "hard evidence" of a new type of pneumonia in their laboratory

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Lab Techs are GONNA spend the next 24 hours in the virus lab. Sleepless nights here are associated with the lives of more than 20 million Shanghai residents.

By Wong Ki

Two epidemiologists, a private car, and a special box, sealed to the standard a pack of highly pathogenic pathogenic microorganisms, contained a sample of a suspected COVID-19 pneumonia patient.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In extraordinary times, in addition to the city's medical institutions, the Shanghai Center for Disease Control and Prevention, is another "not closed" institutions

The box was delivered to the biological sample collection room of the quality control department of the Shanghai CDC, where samples of suspected cases received twice a day were sent to the virus detection laboratory. Normally, 24 hours later, a sample's conclusion about the presence of COVID-19 can be reported from the lab, providing the most critical evidence for follow up treatment.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Samples of pneumonia cases suspected of COVID-19 infection are being transported at the Shanghai Center for Disease Control and Prevention

As we weep for the "retrograde" doctor, in a seemingly quiet lab, the CDC's lab inspectors are also working to contain the spread of the new pneumonia as quickly as possible, engaged in high-risk, high-intensity work.

Their work deserves our respect as well!

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This morning, Ying Yong and his team went to the Shanghai Center for Disease Control and Prevention, visited the center's laboratory, and connected with the staff who were testing the nucleic acid of the virus. Ying Yong called for scientific and effective prevention and control of the epidemic, the formulation of comprehensive prevention and control measures to guide the grass roots to carry out prevention and control work

To confirm COVID-19 pneumonia,

Damn it, they're gonNA give us the smoking gun

"I put on my hazmat suit and went into the lab yesterday at 8:00, finished the first samples at 2:30 and went out for lunch. Li Chongshan, deputy director of the Shanghai Center for Disease Control and Prevention's Institute of biological testing for Pathogens, said: Working in the laboratory 24 hours yesterday, I continue to work in the office today —————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————— --.

A definitive diagnosis of COVID-19 pneumonia requires a critical laboratory test, Li said. According to the National Health and Health Commission's plan for the prevention and control of pneumonia caused by COVID-19 infection (for trial implementation) , all laboratory testing for pneumonia caused by COVID-19 infection in Shanghai is undertaken by the city's Center for Disease Control and Prevention. In other words, samples of suspected patients found in hospitals around the city were collected by doctors and eventually sent to the virus testing laboratory of the Shanghai Center for Disease Control and Prevention.

Since January 16 to 8 days, the laboratory has never turned off the lights, the virus detection laboratory has prepared a total of seven groups of detection personnel, each class of 6-8 people, a 24-hour shift.

In recent days, the sample size in the whole city was basically stable in more than 30 cases, with two samples per case —— Throat Swab and nasal swab of patients. This means that each shift of laboratory workers is exposed to dozens of samples of suspected COVID-19 pneumonia cases.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Each sample is tested in five main steps: 1. The Examiners Mark and package the samples; 2. NUCLEIC ACID extraction; 3. Preparation of fluorescent quantitative PCR system; 4. On-machine testing; 5. Output Judgment Report. Of the five main steps, the first three require manual operation.

"there is a high risk in laboratory testing, but we will strictly protect it, regulate the operation and control the risk to zero, " Li said. Currently, the samples are tested with nucleic acid detection technology, according to the COVID-19, nucleic acid testing is conducted in P2 laboratories, where each tester is given a biosafety level 3 personal protection.

Isolation suits that will be wet in more than 10 minutes,
They have to wear it for more than six hours

Isolation suits that will be wet in more than 10 minutes,

They have to wear it for more than six hours

Today is New Year's Eve, according to schedule, Zhou Yanqiu, Cui Xinyi, Chu Wei, Min Chen, Chen Weixin Laboratory testers, will spend 24 hours in the virus detection laboratory. Sleepless nights here are associated with the lives of more than 20 million Shanghai residents.

According to academician Zhong Nanshan, the current COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic is still in a "uphill" phase, which means that in recent days, confirmed patients will continue to increase, and the rate of increase may be significantly accelerated. For Examiners, the battle in the lab will not be halted by the Spring Festival.

Li Chongshan told the reporter that the biological safety three-level protective clothing will get wet after wearing the clothes inside for more than 10 minutes, and according to the current workload, they have to work continuously for more than six hours before they can take off the protective clothing to rest. "We joke that it's called a free sauna. "

According to reports, in order to deal with the epidemic of pneumonia caused by COVID-19 infection, the Shanghai Center for Disease Control and Prevention mobilized other laboratory cadres and personnel from the district-level Center for Disease Control and Prevention to reinforce virus detection laboratories, at present, 25 staff members are involved in the shift of virus detection laboratory. "Chu Wei and Chen Weixin in the New Year's Eve class are the business backbone drawn from the Huangpu District CDC and the Jiading District District CDC, respectively. "

The average age of the test team was 35, with the youngest being 25, Li said. Most of them have a medical education, and more than half of them have master's or doctoral degrees. Received the task of the epidemic, 9 people voluntarily gave up the plan to go home for the new year, without hesitation to stay at work.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
It is these twenty-odd young laboratory professionals who undertake the task of laboratory testing of pneumonia samples from all COVID-19 patients in Shanghai to find "hard evidence" for the cause of each patient.

It's well-planned and methodical

On the evening of January 20, the COVID-19 confirmed Shanghai's first imported case of pneumonia. But as early as January 14, Shanghai CDC had already begun preparing samples of pneumonia for possible COVID-19.

"On January 14, the National Health Commission issued relevant guidelines, and our center immediately started the emergency procurement process for reagents and consumables, and prepared materials for the detection of COVID-19 pneumonia samples, " Li said, adding that in addition to preparing materials, earlier, director Zhang Xi and director Teng Zheng began training lab staff at the two levels of CDC in the city to ensure that all processes and personnel could deal with pneumonia cases in Shanghai, where COVID-19 infection occurred.

From the tone of Li Chongshan, the reporter does not hear flustered exhaustion, more is methodical. "In recent years, under the leadership of the municipal government and the guidance of the Municipal Health Commission, we have carried out four rounds of the three-year action plan for the construction of the public health system, and achieved remarkable results. The technology for pathogen detection has made great progress. Shanghai CDC has a comprehensive emergency response plan for dealing with new outbreaks of infectious diseases. We have also carried out a number of major national special studies. The efficiency and accuracy of our laboratory tests are among the highest in the country and are not bad compared with developed countries. "We, the CDC, will spare no effort to win the battle against COVID-19 pneumonia. We are confident that we will ensure the safety and health of the people. "
